findings.suggestion:
Wrap the desktopCapturer call in try/catch. Log the error with context (e.g., 'Screenshot capture failed') using the project's structured logger, then either re-throw a typed error (e.g., CaptureError) or return a Result type. Example:
try {
  const sources = await desktopCapturer.getSources({...})
  ...
} catch (error) {
  log.error('Screenshot capture failed', { error })
  throw new CaptureError('desktopCapturer.getSources failed', { cause: error })
}

